1.  install  centos linux.

1.1 readme first 
1.1.1 English https://wiki.centos.org/Manuals/ReleaseNotes/CentOS6.7
1.1.2 Chinese https://wiki.centos.org/zh/Manuals/ReleaseNotes/CentOS6.7
1.2 download a centos DVD 
http://mirrors.aliyun.com/centos/6.7/isos/x86_64/CentOS-6.7-x86_64-bin-DVD1.iso

1.2 install centos on usb disk

1.2.1  make a install usb disk with Win32DiskImager under Windows OS
https://sourceforge.net/projects/win32diskimager/files/latest/download

1.2.2  make a install usb disk with DD under Linux OS
dd  if=/image/CentOS-6.7-x86_64-bin-DVD1.iso  of=/dev/usb-media

1.2.3  install centos with  "mini desktop" SET

2. install VGA driver with OpenCL support.

2.1 download nvidia driver  (nvidia VGA card is the first choice with your computer)
2.2 download nvidia OpenCL SDK

3. install Agisoft Photoscan Pro 

3.1 download photoscan
3.2 setup photoscan
3.2.1 Server host
3.2.2 Node host
